Do you think it will mean even more additional employment for the people in the United States?

24:20.200 --> 24:25.560
Well, I wish though, Sun Gerrit, I think it's very hard to kind of prove anything about

24:25.560 --> 24:32.180
the future because the future is rather inscrutable and so much depends on the general level of

24:32.180 --> 24:35.320
the economic activity of the trading partners.

24:35.320 --> 24:39.520
But we know that we're going to be worse than in our position if we're not able to deal

24:39.520 --> 24:41.320
with the common market.

24:41.320 --> 24:47.280
And I think we have the opportunity of enhancing our export position in this market because

24:47.280 --> 24:49.080
it has to big demand factor.

24:49.080 --> 24:52.120
It is growing so rapidly and it is our most important.

24:52.120 --> 24:55.160
Now, of course, some industries are going to be adversely affected.

24:55.160 --> 25:02.600
We know that because in some they perhaps can manufacture things in other countries so

25:02.600 --> 25:04.640
reasonably than we can.

25:04.640 --> 25:10.000
All their provisions and the bill for taking care of these adversely affected.

25:10.000 --> 25:17.420
And I think that the proposal in the trade expansion act make better provisions for

25:17.420 --> 25:23.840
these possibilities and have ever been suggested to the Congress before because there's a program

25:23.840 --> 25:31.480
of trade adjustment assistance whereby small firms, if they're hurt by import competition,

25:31.480 --> 25:36.120
can obtain governmental assistance in the forms of loans.

25:36.120 --> 25:40.200
And workers, if they're unemployed or if they find they're under employed because of

25:40.200 --> 25:46.160
import competition, can obtain the allowances which will permit them to be retrained for jobs

25:46.160 --> 25:48.600
in which they can better compete.

25:48.600 --> 25:52.720
But I don't think really where going to feel these hurts.

25:52.720 --> 25:57.200
In the first place, this program will go into effect only very gradually.

25:57.200 --> 26:02.800
The act has the odds that any reductions in tariffs may not be put into effect in a period

26:02.800 --> 26:04.320
of less than five years.

26:04.320 --> 26:08.440
So this gives a lot of time for, and I just a normal adjustment.

26:08.440 --> 26:13.000
And of course the big thing that appeals to me and I think all Americans is that by having

26:13.000 --> 26:20.000
a great trading area that we are gaining in strength as against the Soviet bloc.

26:20.000 --> 26:24.560
And I think it might be well to hear the President again as to what this kind of leadership

26:24.560 --> 26:25.240
means.

27:04.320 --> 27:22.360
Well, I know that Mr. Kruyshev doesn't want to see this common market become a reality

27:22.360 --> 27:23.560
and he doesn't want to be sweating.

27:23.560 --> 27:28.960
He's fighting it to come a part of it because that means that economically and industrially

27:28.960 --> 27:34.420
and in all kinds of strength we'll have a much greater advantage over the communist

27:34.420 --> 27:37.560
bloc block and therefore a better chance for peace in the world, doesn't it?

27:37.560 --> 27:39.600
I still only believe that, sir.

27:39.600 --> 27:44.560
Well, thank you very much, Mr. Peterson, for being with us and that's all for this

27:44.560 --> 27:57.280
time, friends.

27:57.280 --> 28:02.080
This is Estes' Keefe over speaking and I'm happy to say a few words in behalf of my

28:02.080 --> 28:07.840
very good friend and my able colleague in the United States Senate Wayne Morris.

28:07.840 --> 28:13.160
Senator Morris and I have shared many fights for worthwhile causes in the Senate and I have

28:13.160 --> 28:18.720
always been proud to stand shoulder to shoulder with him in these efforts.

28:18.720 --> 28:24.240
He enjoys the highest regard of his colleagues, the cost of his courage and his great devotion

28:24.240 --> 28:25.920
to principle.

28:25.920 --> 28:30.160
Let me tell you about a special talent for hard work that is one of Senator Morris's

28:30.160 --> 28:33.120
many able qualifications.

28:33.120 --> 28:37.120
I have the privilege of being a member of the Senate Armed Services Committee.

28:37.120 --> 28:43.320
I know firsthand about Senator Morris's diligent work and his testimony and behalf of

28:43.320 --> 28:47.000
appropriations to be made for the state of Oregon.

28:47.000 --> 28:52.840
I have jotted down some of the highlights in the last few years of Senator Morris's effort

28:52.840 --> 28:58.680
to effectively pursue and persuade the getting of appropriations for great projects in

28:58.680 --> 29:00.200
the state of Oregon.

29:00.200 --> 29:01.920
Let me list just a few.

29:01.920 --> 29:06.960
In the nature of public works, there are many great bams under construction which he

29:06.960 --> 29:12.280
has fought far successfully in the Senate and before the appropriations committee.

29:12.280 --> 29:20.040
John Day, Krueger, Green Peter, Hills Creek and of course recently the 40-foot channel

29:20.040 --> 29:25.280
on the Columbia which means so much to Portland and to that section generally.

29:25.280 --> 29:31.200
In range work, he has fought for special appropriations for receding burned ranges.

29:31.200 --> 29:38.840
This year he obtained funds to begin a model range rehabilitation program in eastern Oregon.

29:38.840 --> 29:43.400
Senator Morris has framed the appropriations committee with the material to support appropriations

29:43.400 --> 29:51.800
for water pollution control, hospital construction in the nation and in Oregon also.

29:51.800 --> 29:59.240
His work to increase forest access road construction in the national forest is not matched by that

29:59.240 --> 30:01.080
of any other senator.

30:01.080 --> 30:06.240
I think it would be difficult to find another member of the United States Senate who does

30:06.240 --> 30:12.760
more than Senator Wayne Morris does to protect the economy and the welfare of the state that

30:12.760 --> 30:15.120
he so ably represents.

30:15.120 --> 30:20.440
Oregon and the nation need Wayne Morris and the Senate and I hope that you are going

30:20.440 --> 30:21.440
to keep them there.

30:21.440 --> 30:22.200
Thank you.

